  <h1>
   date_inc_month
  </h1>
  With this function you can increment a given datetime value by a specific number of months, and it will return the new datetime value.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">date_inc_month( date, amount );
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      date
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Maths_And_Numbers/Date_And_Time/date_current_datetime.htm">
        Datetime
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The datetime to add to.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      amount
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The number of months (must be an integer) to add.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">mynewdatetime = date_inc_month(date_current_datetime(), 12);
</code></pre>
  This would set "mynewdatetime" to the current date but with 12 months added.
 </body>
</html>